# Documentation: First Policy with Templates & Examples

## Documentation-First Rule

### When to Apply
- Non-trivial code changes
- New APIs
- Complex logic
- External integrations

### Documentation Requirements
- **Always consult official documentation** before making decisions
- **Prefer official docs over blogs**
- **Required references** in PRs/code for non-trivial logic:
  - TypeScript (official docs)
  - MDN (JavaScript reference)
  - Official docs for any runtime/framework/libraries used (e.g., Node.js, React) as applicable

### Agent Behavior
- Before assuming behavior of an API, include the doc link and a ≤25-word quote when the change relies on it
- Always update CHANGELOG.md and README.md as changes are made
- Keep documentation in sync with code changes

## Templates & Examples

### Commit Message Template

```
feat(transactions): add transaction reconciliation

- Implement automatic reconciliation algorithm
- Add reconciliation status field to Transaction entity
- Add unit tests for reconciliation edge cases

Closes #123
```

### Branch Naming Convention

```
feat/transactions-add-reconciliation
fix/auth-csrf-token
chore/scripts-add-db-backup
```

### PR Checklist Template

* [ ] Commits follow Angular conventional commits
* [ ] All tests pass locally and in CI
* [ ] Quality checks ran successfully
* [ ] Scripts used where applicable
* [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated with all changes
* [ ] README.md updated if behavior changed
* [ ] Documentation kept in sync with code changes
* [ ] Security scan completed

### Response Header Template (Agent/Human Automation)

```
Timestamp: 2025-09-09T21:00:00-03:00
Path: /src/features/transactions/reconciliation.ts
Command: ./scripts/dev.sh test
Summary: added reconciliation algorithm + tests
```

## Documentation Standards

### Code Documentation
- Minimize comments; explain the "why" when non-obvious
- Let code express the "what" through clear naming
- Document trade-offs briefly when deviating from ideal patterns
- Include doc links and quotes when changes rely on external APIs

### Project Documentation
- **CHANGELOG.md**: Update with all changes
- **README.md**: Update if behavior changed
- **API Documentation**: Keep in sync with code changes
- **Architecture Decisions**: Document significant design choices

### Documentation Maintenance
- Keep documentation in sync with code changes
- Regular review and updates
- Version documentation when making significant changes
- Use semantic versioning for documentation updates

## Documentation Best Practices

### Writing Guidelines
- Clear and concise language
- Include examples where helpful
- Reference official documentation
- Keep documentation up-to-date

### Organization
- Group related documentation together
- Use consistent formatting and structure
- Include navigation and cross-references
- Maintain a logical information hierarchy

### Maintenance
- Regular review cycles
- Update documentation with code changes
- Remove outdated information
- Keep examples current and working
